{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1aff224d-f435-4595-b028-35a205e05495","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — **remove it**. It was the .NET 9 opt-in flag. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` talks to MTP natively; the property is redundant.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — **keep it**. This tells MSTest to build your test project as an MTP executable, which is still required.\n- Everything else (your `MSTest` package ref, `OutputType Exe`) looks correct.\n\nYour updated project:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — no extra configuration needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8505e804-ee1b-4ddf-b312-47f14a86d83f","outputTokens":210,"requestId":"67C5:2ED2CA:28FB9FD:2D5C426:69FD3687"},"id":"c201a60a-eeba-45ac-840d-d9957536a9d0","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:04:12.648Z","parentId":"426d1c94-f323-4161-bde5-eb403befcdbe"}
